# ── Demo vs live ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Demo mode (the default when auth isn't configured) needs NO variables at all:
# no sign-in, role switcher visible, OTP flow accepts code 123456, data in
# server memory. Set DEMO_MODE=true to force demo even with everything below
# configured (useful for a dedicated demo deployment); DEMO_MODE=false to
# force live.
# DEMO_MODE=

# ── Database (Phase 1) ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Postgres connection string (Vercel Postgres / Neon / Supabase). Without it,
# all data (journeys, content overrides, organisations, users) is in-memory
# and resets when the server restarts.
# DATABASE_URL=postgres://user:password@host:5432/dbname

# ── File storage (Phase 1) ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Vercel Blob read-write token. Without it, uploaded documents, videos, and
# guide PDFs are inlined as base64 data URLs (demo only).
# BLOB_READ_WRITE_TOKEN=

# ── Auth (Phase 2) — all four required for live phone sign-in ────────────────
# Random 32+ char secret for signing session JWTs (e.g. `openssl rand -hex 32`).
# AUTH_SECRET=
# From the Twilio console: Account SID + Auth Token, and the SID of a
# Verify Service (Verify > Services > Create; enable SMS channel).
# TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID=
# TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN=
# TWILIO_VERIFY_SERVICE_SID=

# Comma-separated E.164 phone numbers that get the admin role on first
# sign-in (access to /admin/* in live mode).
# ADMIN_PHONES=+61400123456
